@* A GENERIC leaf display (decision 135). Its parameter's type is the type parameter T, not a
   concrete type -- Blazor infers T at the call site from Value="@expr". The value it renders was
   TYPED by the parent; the child sees only T, which erases. This is the exact shape register A15
   is about: a float/decimal/DateTime crossing @typeparam must keep its type-directed formatter. *@
@typeparam T

<span>@Value</span>

@code {
    [Parameter] public T? Value { get; set; }
}
